description: Numbers with the property that, when expressed in base 8 and then interpreted in base 10, a multiple of the original number is obtained.
comments: Decimal 'base 8 looking' numbers divided by their actual base 8 value is an integer.There are only 37 terms up to 30 million. - _Harvey P. Dale_, Sep 29 2012
links: Harvey P. Dale, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..37
example: 7 in base 8 is 7, which interpreted in base 10 is 7=1*7
author: _Patrick De Geest_, april 1998.
extensions: Edited by _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jun 07 2008 at the suggestion of _Sergio Pimentel_
